<statement>
<p>Graph the parabola <m>\displaystyle{y}=-{8}{\left({x}-{2}\right)}^{{2}}-{1}</m></p>
<p>The vertex is <fillin characters="7" /> Â </p>
<image width="52%"  pi:generated="problems/images/d1d6d254a38d38a1280bab7f4e8b38b1.png" />


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{1}\right)}</m></li><li><image width="52%"  pi:generated="problems/images/e7ebf08029c8266631a107e50de86345.png" />
</li></ul></p><p>The form of a parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}={a}{\left({x}-{h}\right)}^{{2}}+{k}</m>. Because this parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}=-{8}{\left({x}-{2}\right)}^{{2}}-{1}</m>, which can be written <m>\displaystyle{y}=-{8}{\left({x}-{\left({2}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left(-{1}\right)}</m> we know the following.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{h}={2}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{k}=-{1}</m>. Thus the vertex is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{1}\right)}</m>.</p>
<p>To graph the parabola we can use the vertex and another convenient point. One convenient point is at <m>\displaystyle{x}={2}+{1}={3}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{8}{\left({3}-{\left({2}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left(-{1}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle=-{8}{\left({1}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left(-{1}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle=-{8}+{\left(-{1}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle=-{9}</m>.</p>
<p>We use <m>\displaystyle{\left({3},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>
</solution>
